<span id="freeTextContainer13912256386198998236">&quot;The School for Scandal&quot; is Richard Brinsley Sheridan&apos;s classic comedy that pokes fun at London upper class society in the late 1700s. Often referred to as a &quot;comedy of manners&quot;, &quot;The School for Scandal&quot; is one Sheridan&apos;s most performed plays and a classic of English comedic drama.</span>
